{"extract_id":"extract_20df7da89e7a429b9cf5791d0ebb2289","results":[{"url":"https://snowflakechronicles.medium.com/snowflake-cost-intelligence-from-raw-telemetry-to-enterprise-finops-governance-af01bda19b4c","title":"Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance | by Satish Kumar | Feb, 2026 | Medium","publish_date":"2026-02-21","excerpts":["Sitemap\n[Open in app](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.medium.reader&referrer=utm_source%3DmobileNavBar&source=post_page---top_nav_layout_nav-----------------------------------------)\n[](https://medium.com/?source=post_page---top_nav_layout_nav-----------------------------------------)\nGet app\n[Write](https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---top_nav_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_topnav------------------)\n[Search](https://medium.com/search?source=post_page---top_nav_layout_nav-----------------------------------------)\n ... \nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance\nContent:\nCloud data platforms promise elasticity and efficiency — but **without continuous visibility and governance, costs can spiral quickly** .\nSnowflake provides exceptionally rich telemetry through `ACCOUNT_USAGE` . However, **raw system tables alone are not sufficient** to build a production-grade FinOps framework.\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\nTo enable **true enterprise cost governance** , we need:\nA **semantic cost model**\nQuery-level **credit attribution**\nStorage intelligence\nML-powered **anomaly detection**\nAutomated **spending alerts**\n**Real-time interactive dashboards**\nIn this article, we design and implement a **fully native, production-grade Snowflake Cost Intelligence Platform** — delivering **complete cost observability, governance, and optimization** , all inside Snowflake.\nSection Title: ... > End-to-End Architecture — Snowflake Cost Intelligence Platform\nContent:\n```\nACCOUNT_USAGE  \n      ↓  \n Semantic Cost Model (YAML + Views)  \n      ↓  \n Snowpark Python + ML  \n      ↓  \n Streamlit Dashboard  ←→  Cost Alert Procedures  \n      ↓  \n FinOps + Platform + Leadership Teams\n```\nThis architecture ensures:\nZero data movement\nNative RBAC security\nEnterprise scalability\nProduction-grade governance\nSection Title: ... > Step 1 — Why Semantic Modeling for Cost Intelligence?\nContent:\nSnowflake exposes detailed cost telemetry, but:\nRaw tables are **complex**\nCost signals are **scattered**\nDashboards require **heavy SQL transformations**\nGovernance teams need **business-friendly KPIs**\nA **semantic model layer** provides:\nConsistent KPIs\nReusable business metrics\nOptimized dashboard performance\nCentralized cost governance logic\n ... \nSection Title: ... > Step 3 — Semantic Model Definition (Production YAML)\nContent:\n```\nname: snowflake_cost_analysis  \ndescription: Semantic model for Snowflake cost analysis including AI/ML services, credit consumption, and spending alerts  \n  \ntables:  \n  # ===========================================  \n  # CORE METERING & COMPUTE  \n  # ===========================================  \n  - name: METERING_SUMMARY  \n    description: Hourly credit usage by service type and object  \n    base_table:  \n      database: SNOWFLAKE  \n      schema: ACCOUNT_USAGE  \n      table: METERING_HISTORY  \n    dimensions:  \n      - name: SERVICE_TYPE  \n        expr: service_type  \n        description: Type of Snowflake service (WAREHOUSE_METERING, CLOUD_SERVICES, AI_SERVICES, etc.)\n ... \nSection Title: ... > Step 3 — Semantic Model Definition (Production YAML)\nContent:\ndata_type: TIMESTAMP_LTZ  \n    measures:  \n      - name: WAREHOUSE_CREDITS  \n        expr: SUM(credits_used)  \n        description: Total warehouse credits  \n        data_type: NUMBER  \n      - name: WAREHOUSE_COMPUTE_CREDITS  \n        expr: SUM(credits_used_compute)  \n        description: Warehouse compute credits  \n        data_type: NUMBER  \n  \n  - name: STORAGE_USAGE  \n    description: Database storage consumption  \n    base_table:  \n      database: SNOWFLAKE  \n      schema: ACCOUNT_USAGE  \n      table: DATABASE_STORAGE_USAGE_HISTORY  \n    dimensions:  \n      - name: DATABASE_NAME  \n        expr: database_name  \n        description: Name of the database  \n        data_type: VARCHAR  \n    time_dimensions:  \n      - name: USAGE_DATE  \n        expr: usage_date  \n        description: Date of storage usage  \n        data_type: DATE  \n    measures:  \n      - name: DATABASE_BYTES  \n        expr: SUM(average_database_bytes)\n ... \nSection Title: ... > Step 3 — Semantic Model Definition (Production YAML)\nContent:\nbase_table:  \n      database: SNOWFLAKE  \n      schema: ACCOUNT_USAGE  \n      table: CORTEX_AISQL_USAGE_HISTORY  \n    dimensions:  \n      - name: FUNCTION_NAME  \n        expr: function_name  \n        description: Name of the Cortex AI function  \n        data_type: VARCHAR  \n      - name: MODEL_NAME  \n        expr: model_name  \n        description: AI model used (llama, mistral, etc.)\n ... \nSection Title: ... > Step 3 — Semantic Model Definition (Production YAML)\nContent:\nSUM(request_count)  \n        description: Number of analyst requests  \n        data_type: NUMBER  \n  \n  - name: CORTEX_AGENT_USAGE  \n    description: Cortex Agent (Snowflake Intelligence) usage  \n    base_table:  \n      database: SNOWFLAKE  \n      schema: ACCOUNT_USAGE  \n      table: CORTEX_AGENT_USAGE_HISTORY  \n    dimensions:  \n      - name: USER_NAME  \n        expr: user_name  \n        description: User who invoked the agent  \n        data_type: VARCHAR  \n      - name: REQUEST_ID  \n        expr: request_id  \n        description: Unique request identifier  \n        data_type: VARCHAR  \n      - name: USAGE_DATE  \n        expr: DATE(start_time)  \n        description: Date of usage  \n        data_type: DATE  \n    time_dimensions:  \n      - name: START_TIME  \n        expr: start_time  \n        description: Start of agent request  \n        data_type: TIMESTAMP_LTZ  \n    measures:  \n      - name: AGENT_CREDITS  \n        expr:\n ... \nSection Title: ... > Step 3 — Semantic Model Definition (Production YAML)\nContent:\n- name: FINE_TUNING_TOKENS  \n        expr: SUM(tokens)  \n        description: Tokens processed in fine-tuning  \n        data_type: NUMBER  \n  \n  # ===========================================  \n  # DOCUMENT PROCESSING  \n  # ===========================================  \n  - name: DOCUMENT_PROCESSING_USAGE  \n    description: Cortex Document Processing (PARSE_DOCUMENT, AI_EXTRACT) usage  \n    base_table:  \n      database: SNOWFLAKE  \n      schema: ACCOUNT_USAGE  \n      table: CORTEX_DOCUMENT_PROCESSING_USAGE_HISTORY  \n    dimensions:  \n      - name: FUNCTION_NAME  \n        expr: function_name  \n        description: Document processing function used  \n        data_type: VARCHAR  \n      - name: MODEL_NAME  \n        expr: model_name  \n        description: Model used for processing  \n        data_type: VARCHAR  \n      - name: USAGE_DATE  \n        expr: DATE(start_time)  \n        description: Date of usage  \n        data_type: DATE\nSection Title: ... > Step 3 — Semantic Model Definition (Production YAML)\nContent:\ntime_dimensions:  \n      - name: START_TIME  \n        expr: start_time  \n        description: Start of processing  \n        data_type: TIMESTAMP_LTZ  \n    measures:  \n      - name: DOC_PROCESSING_CREDITS  \n        expr: SUM(credits_used)  \n        description: Credits consumed for document processing  \n        data_type: NUMBER  \n      - name: PAGE_COUNT  \n        expr: SUM(page_count)  \n        description: Number of pages processed  \n        data_type: NUMBER  \n      - name: DOCUMENT_COUNT  \n        expr: SUM(document_count)  \n        description: Number of documents processed  \n        data_type: NUMBER  \n  \n  - name: DOCUMENT_AI_USAGE  \n    description: Document AI usage (deprecated - legacy)  \n    base_table:  \n      database: SNOWFLAKE  \n      schema: ACCOUNT_USAGE  \n      table: DOCUMENT_AI_USAGE_HISTORY  \n    dimensions:  \n      - name: OPERATION_NAME  \n        expr: operation_name  \n        description: Document AI\n ... \nSection Title: ... > Step 3 — Semantic Model Definition (Production YAML)\nContent:\nACCOUNT_USAGE  \n      table: CORTEX_FUNCTIONS_USAGE_HISTORY  \n    dimensions:  \n      - name: FUNCTION_NAME  \n        expr: function_name  \n        description: Cortex function name  \n        data_type: VARCHAR  \n      - name: MODEL_NAME  \n        expr: model_name  \n        description: Model used  \n        data_type: VARCHAR  \n      - name: USAGE_DATE  \n        expr: DATE(start_time)  \n        description: Date of usage  \n        data_type: DATE  \n    time_dimensions:  \n      - name: START_TIME  \n        expr: start_time  \n        description: Start of usage window  \n        data_type: TIMESTAMP_LTZ  \n    measures:  \n      - name: FUNCTION_CREDITS  \n        expr: SUM(token_credits)  \n        description: Credits consumed  \n        data_type: NUMBER  \n      - name: FUNCTION_TOKENS  \n        expr: SUM(tokens)  \n        description: Tokens processed  \n        data_type: NUMBER  \n  \n  \n  \n#\n ... \nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance > Alert Procedure\nContent:\n```\nCREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS COST_ANALYTICS;  \n  \nCREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS COST_ANALYTICS.MODELS;  \n  \nCREATE STAGE IF NOT EXISTS COST_ANALYTICS.MODELS.SEMANTIC_MODELS;  \n  \nCREATE OR REPLACE NOTIFICATION INTEGRATION COST_ALERT_EMAIL_INT  \n    TYPE = EMAIL  \n    ENABLED = TRUE  \n    ALLOWED_RECIPIENTS = ('skxx2014@gmail.com');  \n  \n--Create Cost Alerts Log Table   \ncreate or replace TABLE COST_ANALYTICS.MODELS.COST_ALERTS_LOG (  \n ID NUMBER(38,0) NOT NULL autoincrement start 1 increment 1 noorder,  \n LOG_TIMESTAMP TIMESTAMP_NTZ(9) DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(),  \n LOG_DATE DATE DEFAULT CURRENT_DATE(),  \n DAILY_CREDITS NUMBER(12,2),  \n WEEKLY_CREDITS NUMBER(12,2),  \n MTD_CREDITS NUMBER(12,2),  \n ROLLING_7DAY_AVG NUMBER(12,2),  \n PROJECTED_MONTHLY NUMBER(12,2),  \n BUDGET_PCT NUMBER(8,2),  \n WOW_CHANGE_PCT NUMBER(8,2),  \n ANOMALY_COUNT NUMBER(38,0),  \n SPIKE_COUNT NUMBER(38,0),\n ... \nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance > Alert Procedure\nContent:\n('snowflake-snowpark-python')  \nHANDLER = 'main'  \nEXECUTE AS CALLER  \nAS  \n$$  \nfrom datetime import datetime  \n  \ndef safe_float(val, default=0.0):  \n    try:  \n        return float(val) if val is not None else default  \n    except:  \n        return default  \n  \ndef safe_int(val, default=0):  \n    try:  \n        return int(val) if val is not None else default  \n    except:  \n        return default  \n  \ndef escape_sql(s):  \n    if s is None:  \n        return \"\"  \n    return str(s).replace(\"'\", \"''\").replace(\"\\\\\", \"\\\\\\\\\")  \n  \ndef safe_query(session, sql, default_row=None):  \n    try:  \n        result = session.sql(sql).collect()  \n        return result if result else default_row  \n    except:  \n        return default_row  \n  \ndef main(session, email_recipient: str, daily_threshold: float = 100, weekly_threshold: float = 500,  \n         rolling_avg_multiplier: float = 2, monthly_budget:\n ... \nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance > Alert Procedure\nContent:\n{round(budget_pct,2)}, {round(wow_change,2)}, {anomaly_count}, {spike_count},   \n         '{escape_sql(top_wh_str)}', '{escape_sql(top_users_str)}', '{escape_sql(svc_str)}',   \n         '{escape_sql(alerts_str)}', {len(alerts)}, {len(alerts) > 0}, '{escape_sql(email_recipient)}',  \n         {total_ai_credits}, '{escape_sql(ml_breakdown_str)}')  \n    \"\"\").collect()  \n  \n    if not alerts:  \n        return f\"OK: Daily={daily_credits}, Weekly={weekly_credits}, TotalAI={total_ai_credits}, Budget={round(budget_pct,1)}%\"  \n  \n    alert_rows = \"\".join([f\"<tr><td style='padding:12px;border-bottom:1px solid #ddd;font-weight:bold;color:{a[2]};'>{a[0]}</td><td style='padding:12px;border-bottom:1px solid #ddd;'>{a[1]}</td></tr>\" for a in alerts])  \n  \n    max_trend = max([r['CREDITS'] for r in trend_result], default=1) or 1  \n    trend_rows = \"\".join([f\"<tr><td\n ... \nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance > Alert Procedure\nContent:\n>= budget_alert_pct else \"\"  \n    budget_bar = min(budget_pct, 100)  \n  \n    ml_section = f'''<div style=\"padding:20px;\"><h2 style=\"color:;border-bottom:2px solid #9c27b0;padding-bottom:10px;\">Top AI SQL Functions</h2><table style=\"width:100%;\"><tr><th style=\"text-align:left;padding:8px;\">Function</th><th style=\"text-align:left;padding:8px;\">Model</th><th style=\"padding:8px;\">Usage</th><th style=\"text-align:right;padding:8px;\">Credits</th></tr>{ml_rows}</table></div>''' if ml_rows else ''  \n    agent_section = f'''<div style=\"padding:20px;background:;\"><h2 style=\"color:;border-bottom:2px solid #673ab7;padding-bottom:10px;\">Top Cortex Agent Users</h2><table style=\"width:100%;\"><tr><th style=\"text-align:left;padding:8px;\">User</th><th style=\"text-align:left;padding:8px;\">Requests</th><th style=\"padding:8px;\">Usage</th><th\nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance > Alert Procedure\nContent:\nstyle=\"text-align:right;padding:8px;\">Credits</th></tr>{agent_rows}</table></div>''' if agent_rows else ''  \n  \n    html = f'''<html><body style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;background:;margin:0;padding:20px;\">  \n<div style=\"max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;background:white;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;\">  \n<div style=\"background:;color:white;padding:25px;\"><h1 style=\"margin:0;\">Snowflake Cost Governance</h1><p style=\"margin:8px 0 0;opacity:0.9;\">{account} - {run_time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')} UTC</p></div>  \n<div style=\"background:;color:white;padding:15px;text-align:center;font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;\">{len(alerts)} ALERT{'S' if len(alerts)>1 else ''} TRIGGERED</div>  \n<div style=\"padding:20px;\"><h2 style=\"color:;border-bottom:2px solid #2d5a87;padding-bottom:10px;\">Alerts</h2><table style=\"width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;\">{alert_rows}</table></div>  \n<div\nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance > Alert Procedure\nContent:\nstyle=\"padding:20px;background:;\"><h2 style=\"color:;border-bottom:2px solid #2d5a87;padding-bottom:10px;\">Key Metrics</h2>  \n<table style=\"width:100%;text-align:center;\"><tr>  \n<td style=\"padding:15px;\"><div style=\"font-size:32px;font-weight:bold;color:;\">{daily_credits}</div><div style=\"color:;font-size:11px;\">YESTERDAY</div></td>  \n<td style=\"padding:15px;\"><div style=\"font-size:32px;font-weight:bold;color:;\">{weekly_credits}</div><div style=\"color:;font-size:11px;\">LAST 7 DAYS</div></td>  \n<td style=\"padding:15px;\"><div style=\"font-size:32px;font-weight:bold;color:;\">{mtd_credits}</div><div style=\"color:;font-size:11px;\">MTD</div></td>  \n<td style=\"padding:15px;\"><div style=\"font-size:32px;font-weight:bold;color:;\">{round(projected_monthly,0)}</div><div style=\"color:;font-size:11px;\">PROJECTED</div></td>  \n</tr></table></div>  \n<div style=\"padding:20px;background:;\"><h2\nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance > Alert Procedure\nContent:\nstyle=\"color:;border-bottom:2px solid #9c27b0;padding-bottom:10px;\">AI/ML Costs (7-Day)</h2>  \n<table style=\"width:100%;text-align:center;\"><tr>  \n<td style=\"padding:12px;\"><div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:bold;color:;\">{round(total_ai_credits,4)}</div><div style=\"color:;font-size:10px;\">TOTAL AI</div></td>  \n<td style=\"padding:12px;\"><div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:bold;color:;\">{ml_daily}</div><div style=\"color:;font-size:10px;\">AI YESTERDAY</div></td>  \n<td style=\"padding:12px;\"><div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:bold;color:;\">{ml_weekly}</div><div style=\"color:;font-size:10px;\">AI WEEKLY</div></td>  \n</tr></table>  \n<h3 style=\"color:;margin-top:20px;\">Service Breakdown</h3>  \n<table style=\"width:100%;text-align:center;border-collapse:collapse;\">  \n<tr style=\"background:;\">  \n<td style=\"padding:10px;border:1px solid #ce93d8;\"><div\n ... \nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance > Alert Procedure\nContent:\nstyle=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:bold;\">{round(budget_pct,1)}% of {monthly_budget}</div></div></div>  \n<div style=\"padding:20px;background:;\"><h2 style=\"color:;border-bottom:2px solid #2d5a87;padding-bottom:10px;\">7-Day Trend</h2><table style=\"width:100%;\">{trend_rows}</table></div>  \n<div style=\"padding:20px;\"><h2 style=\"color:;border-bottom:2px solid #2d5a87;padding-bottom:10px;\">Top Warehouses</h2><table style=\"width:100%;\">{wh_rows}</table></div>  \n<div style=\"padding:20px;background:;\"><h2 style=\"color:;border-bottom:2px solid #2d5a87;padding-bottom:10px;\">Service Breakdown</h2><table style=\"width:100%;\">{svc_rows}</table></div>  \n<div style=\"padding:20px;\"><h2 style=\"color:;border-bottom:2px solid #2d5a87;padding-bottom:10px;\">Details</h2>  \n<table style=\"width:100%;\">  \n<tr><td\n ... \nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance > Alert Procedure\nContent:\nSYSTEM$SEND_EMAIL('COST_ALERT_EMAIL_INT', '{escape_sql(email_recipient)}', '{subject}', '{html_escaped}', 'text/html')\"\"\").collect()  \n  \n    return f\"ALERTS SENT ({len(alerts)}): {alerts_str} | Total AI: {total_ai_credits}\"  \n$$  \n  \n--Scheduled Task — Automated Daily Execution  \n  \nCREATE OR REPLACE TASK COST_ANALYTICS.MODELS.DAILY_COST_ALERT_TASK  \n    WAREHOUSE = COMPUTE_WH  \n    SCHEDULE = 'USING CRON 0 8 * * * UTC'  -- Daily at 8 AM UTC  \n    COMMENT = 'Daily cost alert check with AI/ML tracking'  \nAS  \nCALL COST_ANALYTICS.MODELS.CHECK_COST_ALERTS(  \n    'skxx2014@gmail.com',   -- EMAIL_RECIPIENT  \n    100,                    -- DAILY_THRESHOLD (credits)  \n    500,                    -- WEEKLY_THRESHOLD (credits)  \n    2,                      -- ROLLING_AVG_MULTIPLIER  \n    1000,                   -- MONTHLY_BUDGET (credits)  \n    80,                     -- BUDGET_ALERT_PCT\n ... \nSection Title: ... > Step 5 — Building the Native Snowflake Streamlit Dashboard\nContent:\nDashboards enable **proactive FinOps intelligence** .\nBy combining:\nSemantic cost models\nSnowpark Python\nStreamlit inside Snowflake\nwe build a **fully native FinOps command center** .\n ... \nSection Title: ... > Step 6 — Production Streamlit Dashboard Code\nContent:\n**Native Snowflake Streamlit application** runs **fully inside Snowsight** :\n ... \nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governance > Step-by-Step Guide\nContent:\nLogin to Snowflake → Open **Snowsight**\nNavigate to **Projects → Streamlit**\nClick **+ Streamlit App**\nConfigure:\nApp Name: `Cost_Analysis_Dashboard`\nWarehouse: `COMPUTE_WH`\nDatabase / Schema: `COST_ANALYTICS.MODELS`\n5. Replace default code with `cost_dashboard.py`\n6. Click **Run**\nYour **real-time FinOps dashboard is now live inside Snowflake** .\nPress enter or click to view image in full size Press enter or click to view image in full size Press enter or click to view image in full size Press enter or click to view image in full size Press enter or click to view image in full size\n ... \nSection Title: Snowflake Cost Intelligence: From Raw Telemetry to Enterprise FinOps Governa
